<paragraph blockId="25.[839,1468,1686,2003]" pageId="25" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis box="[869,979,1686,1710]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="49">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Female: length of compound tergite 1+2 c. 0.67 of that of tergite 3; sternites 1, 2, and 3 large; sternite 4 somewhat smaller; sternites 5 and 6 very short, but sclerotised. Male: sternite 4 with small notch on posterior margin, not cleft; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1239,1803,1827]" captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="26.[627,699,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[121,1422,178,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-80@26.[121,1421,151,1743]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 45–47.Bama monstrans n.sp.(45) Distal part of aedeagus of holotype, right lateral view,scale = 0.3 mm.(46) Preglans from left side, scale = 0.1 mm.(47) Pair of mid coxae of male, left lateroventral view. bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans; pg, lobe of preglans; st, stipe; tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684915/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="49">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
) with preglans (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="26.[627,699,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[121,1422,178,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-80@26.[121,1421,151,1743]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 45–47.Bama monstrans n.sp.(45) Distal part of aedeagus of holotype, right lateral view,scale = 0.3 mm.(46) Preglans from left side, scale = 0.1 mm.(47) Pair of mid coxae of male, left lateroventral view. bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans; pg, lobe of preglans; st, stipe; tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684915/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="49">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) expanded into subovate, partly membranous lobe bearing many peg-like spinules; flexible section large, longer than glans; glans stoutly ovoid with short distal lobe ensheathing hatchet-like sclerite; bulb rather short; left terminal filament c. half as long as glans, right terminal filament conspicuously smaller.
</paragraph>
